        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer810427781" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15718692489850269281">Brendan Poe loves his mom and sister but hates his father. His father, Anson Poe, is an abusive and evil man who grows marijuana on his property. When visiting his mother and sister, Brendan finds his father has poured scathing hot coffee on his mother and Brendan rushes her to the hospital, taking his sister along also. Brendan works at a bar as a bouncer and is in love with Julie March, a bartender and the owner&apos;s daughter. <br/><br/>I don&apos;t want to give any spoilers away so that&apos;s all I&apos;ll say as far a</span>
  <span id="freeText15718692489850269281" style="display:none">Brendan Poe loves his mom and sister but hates his father. His father, Anson Poe, is an abusive and evil man who grows marijuana on his property. When visiting his mother and sister, Brendan finds his father has poured scathing hot coffee on his mother and Brendan rushes her to the hospital, taking his sister along also. Brendan works at a bar as a bouncer and is in love with Julie March, a bartender and the owner's daughter. <br /><br />I don't want to give any spoilers away so that's all I'll say as far as the basic plot. I really enjoyed it but I have to say that with all that was happening in the story I did feel the romance element suffered a bit. Not too much but just not what I expected from Sharon Sala. The story goes back and forth from several people, including the villains. That said, I should add that plot-wise the romance really had to go that way to be more believable. I think that Sharon Sala and Romantic Suspense fans will enjoy it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15718692489850269281" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
