        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer651964202" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4544873427199268756">A THOUSAND LIES excels in every way possible......From the very first word of Chapter One to the very last word of the Epilogue; you are swept up in the magic of Sharon Sala&apos;s story writing. I can&apos;t even begin to tell you how you will be caught up in these characters lives. The characterization is spot on; the emotions of each main character laid bare on the pages......so real that you can feel their pain, their love, their frustrations, their hopes for the future. You cheer most of them on; and</span>
  <span id="freeText4544873427199268756" style="display:none">A THOUSAND LIES excels in every way possible......From the very first word of Chapter One to the very last word of the Epilogue; you are swept up in the magic of Sharon Sala's story writing. I can't even begin to tell you how you will be caught up in these characters lives. The characterization is spot on; the emotions of each main character laid bare on the pages......so real that you can feel their pain, their love, their frustrations, their hopes for the future. You cheer most of them on; and you despise the character of Anson Poe like you've never despised a story character before!<br /><br />There's never a dull moment between the pages of this book! You won't want to put it down, and you won't want it to end!<br /><br />Sharon Sala aka Dinah McCall is one of the most remarkably gifted writers of our time, and she has outdone herself with A THOUSAND LIES!! Bravo!!</span>
