<span id="freeTextContainer7456061963651482667">Another outstanding read from Sharon Sala. I should stop being surprised at this point. I&apos;ve read enough of her books to know better by now. This particular book had the dysfunctional family from hell. The father was truly evil as he was certainly a psychopath along with being a narcissistic monster. Belinda (&quot;Linny&quot;) the young daughter, who is also a victim of her father&apos;s evil, is a small shining star. But, the survivor and hero of the entire book is Brendan. He has a quiet strength and wisdom</span>
  <span id="freeText7456061963651482667" style="display:none">Another outstanding read from Sharon Sala. I should stop being surprised at this point. I've read enough of her books to know better by now. This particular book had the dysfunctional family from hell. The father was truly evil as he was certainly a psychopath along with being a narcissistic monster. Belinda ("Linny") the young daughter, who is also a victim of her father's evil, is a small shining star. But, the survivor and hero of the entire book is Brendan. He has a quiet strength and wisdom beyond his years. I defy anyone reading this book not to fall in love with him. I really enjoyed this book! </span>
