<div id="review_1558668890" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1558668890" />
    <a title="BookMaven" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1319696-bookmaven"><img alt="BookMaven" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1558668890?book_show_action=true">Feb 23, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="BookMaven" class="user" itemprop="url" name="BookMaven" href="/user/show/1319696-bookmaven">BookMaven</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1558668890" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1507004291078064279"><strong>Sharon Sala is a Storyteller Extraordinaire</strong><br/><br/>Brendan Poe knew the day would come when he would have to stop his father from hurting his family. Brendan knew he would probably have to kill him. His father, Anson Poe, was evil personified. He cared for no one, but himself, and he controlled everyone around him with pain and fear. Brendan left home years ago determined not to let his father rule him, but his love for his mother and sister brought him home to visit this day to find that his father had</span>
  <span id="freeText1507004291078064279" style="display:none"><strong>Sharon Sala is a Storyteller Extraordinaire</strong><br /><br />Brendan Poe knew the day would come when he would have to stop his father from hurting his family. Brendan knew he would probably have to kill him. His father, Anson Poe, was evil personified. He cared for no one, but himself, and he controlled everyone around him with pain and fear. Brendan left home years ago determined not to let his father rule him, but his love for his mother and sister brought him home to visit this day to find that his father had purposely poured hot coffee on his mother's feet causing burns that needed immediate attention by a doctor. He scooped his mother up to carry her to his car, and then the hospital. He ordered his 9 year old sister to come with him, too. The day of reckoning had come. Who will survive, Brendan, or Anson?<br /><br />I usually avoid books about evil and violence, but I felt compelled to pick this one up because its setting is New Orleans. I love New Orleans and its aura of mystery, romance, it's unique history and melting pot of cultures. The plot of this book blends all of these elements gripping this reader's heart and mind from beginning to end. The suspense grabs you, not once letting you down. There is a romance that is perfect poetry. The themes of good, evil, loyalty, treachery, family, enemies, spirit and godlessness are masterfully addressed.<br /><br />Author Sala weaves a spellbinding tale that touches every nuance of humanness. There is despair, yet hope, hate, yet love. Sala has an imagination and writing style that mesmerizes her reader. One can hardly put it down! Sala definitely hit the 5 star mark<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1507004291078064279" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


