        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/18108696-a-thousand-lies">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer847939214" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13800532091987467148">This came as a recommendation from a friend on Fb, it was free so I downloaded. I&apos;m not sorry I did. For the most part, it was a good story told well. I liked the characters, especially Belinda and Claudette, but even their well-defined characters did not make up for the lack of likeability in Anson Poe. Even as the villain, I would have liked to have some reason to enjoy following his story. His devious nature was not realistic. Neither was the sickening sweet relationship between Bren and Juli</span>
  <span id="freeText13800532091987467148" style="display:none">This came as a recommendation from a friend on Fb, it was free so I downloaded. I'm not sorry I did. For the most part, it was a good story told well. I liked the characters, especially Belinda and Claudette, but even their well-defined characters did not make up for the lack of likeability in Anson Poe. Even as the villain, I would have liked to have some reason to enjoy following his story. His devious nature was not realistic. Neither was the sickening sweet relationship between Bren and Julie. Love is one thing and I root for that, but their displays were as unbelievable as Anson's evilness. Again, it was a good story, but there were elements I did not buy into.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13800532091987467148" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
