<div id="review_1140162229" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1140162229" />
    <a title="Cheryl" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7438967-cheryl"><img alt="Cheryl" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1140162229?book_show_action=true">Dec 24, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cheryl" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cheryl" href="/user/show/7438967-cheryl">Cheryl</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1140162229" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12046974956154583467"><strong>Wonderful story set in the bayou</strong><br/><br/>Great story about family dynamics, greed and power. Generations of family money, illicit businesses, hush money under the table and feuding families. Does money buy class and prestige? Does it mean you can turn your nose up at those less fortunate? Two wealthy families and the younger generation looking to merge both families. One family headed by an evil father the other headed by a protective and wealthy patriarch. This was a very touching story and the title A </span>
  <span id="freeText12046974956154583467" style="display:none"><strong>Wonderful story set in the bayou</strong><br /><br />Great story about family dynamics, greed and power. Generations of family money, illicit businesses, hush money under the table and feuding families. Does money buy class and prestige? Does it mean you can turn your nose up at those less fortunate? Two wealthy families and the younger generation looking to merge both families. One family headed by an evil father the other headed by a protective and wealthy patriarch. This was a very touching story and the title A Thousand Lies crafts a tale of what those lies can do to a family. Looking forward to reading more of Sharon Sala's books.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12046974956154583467" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
